    <section id="introduction" class="info-section">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>At Tulong Kabataan ("we," "our," or "us"), we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, store, and safeguard data when you use the Tulong Kabataan platform, create an account, donate, organize or support campaigns, volunteer for events, submit in-kind donations, contact support, or interact with our online services.</p>
        <p>This policy is intended to support transparency and responsible handling of personal data under applicable Philippine privacy principles, including the Data Privacy Act of 2012. It should be read together with our Terms of Service and any campaign, event, donation, or verification notices shown on the platform.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="scope" class="info-section">
        <h2>Scope of This Policy</h2>
        <p>This Privacy Policy applies to personal information processed through Tulong Kabataan websites, pages, forms, dashboards, donation tools, event registration flows, in-kind donation tracking, account verification, notifications, chatbot support, and administrative review tools.</p>
        <p>This policy does not replace separate privacy notices from third-party payment processors, social media platforms, email providers, map providers, analytics tools, or partner organizations that may operate their own services. When you leave our platform or use a third-party service, that third party's own terms and privacy policy may apply.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="information-we-collect" class="info-section">
        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide, information generated through your use of the platform, and information necessary for platform security, campaign accountability, and operational coordination.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, birthday, password credentials, profile photo, login method, account status, email verification status, and related account preferences.</li>
            <li><strong>Identity and Verification Information:</strong> Identification type, ID number, birth date, sex, address, uploaded ID images, face photo, selfie, verification request status, reviewer notes, and reupload requests when account verification is required.</li>
            <li><strong>Donation Information:</strong> Campaign selected, donation amount, donor name or account, proof of payment, reference number, payment status, donation history, manual donation requests, and records needed to validate, report, or resolve donation issues.</li>
            <li><strong>Campaign Information:</strong> Campaign title, description, category, target amount, uploaded photos, campaign updates, reports, beneficiary-related details provided by organizers, campaign status, fundraising progress, and organizer account details.</li>
            <li><strong>In-Kind Donation Information:</strong> Item name, category, quantity, description, selected drop-off point, status updates, cancellation records, delivery or coordination notes, and related contact details.</li>
            <li><strong>Volunteer and Event Information:</strong> Event registration details, selected volunteer roles, attendance status, reminders, event participation history, and information needed to coordinate safe and organized volunteer activity.</li>
            <li><strong>Support and Communications:</strong> Messages sent through email, social media, chatbot, contact channels, reports, appeals, feedback, complaints, and any attachments or screenshots you provide to help us resolve an issue.</li>
            <li><strong>Technical and Usage Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device information, pages viewed, timestamps, authentication logs, security events, notification activity, and general platform usage data.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="sensitive-information" class="info-section">
        <h2>Sensitive Information</h2>
        <p>Some platform features may require sensitive personal information, especially for identity verification, fraud prevention, volunteer safety, donation validation, or legal compliance. We only request this information when it is relevant to a platform purpose and we limit access to authorized personnel or service providers who need it to perform their roles.</p>
        <p>Uploaded identification documents, face photos, selfies, payment proof images, and beneficiary-related documents should be submitted only through official Tulong Kabataan channels. Users must not upload documents or images that they are not authorized to share.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="how-we-use-information" class="info-section">
        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect or receive for legitimate platform, safety, legal, and operational purposes, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To create, verify, secure, and manage user accounts.</li>
            <li>To authenticate logins, support Google login, reset passwords, verify email addresses, and prevent unauthorized access.</li>
            <li>To review account verification submissions and reduce fraudulent activity.</li>
            <li>To create, review, publish, pause, reject, end, or monitor campaigns.</li>
            <li>To process donations, manual donation requests, donation reports, payment proof submissions, refunds where applicable, and donation records.</li>
            <li>To coordinate in-kind donations, drop-off points, volunteer events, event registrations, reminders, and attendance records.</li>
            <li>To send administrative messages, notifications, campaign updates, donation confirmations, event reminders, and important policy or security notices.</li>
            <li>To respond to support requests, complaints, safety reports, legal concerns, privacy requests, and user appeals.</li>
            <li>To maintain transparency reports, impact reports, donation summaries, campaign analytics, and accountability records.</li>
            <li>To detect, investigate, prevent, or respond to fraud, impersonation, abuse, harassment, spam, unauthorized fundraising, payment manipulation, and other prohibited activity.</li>
            <li>To comply with applicable laws, lawful requests, recordkeeping obligations, dispute resolution, and platform enforcement.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="legal-bases" class="info-section">
        <h2>Legal Bases for Processing</h2>
        <p>Depending on the feature and context, we may process personal information based on your consent, the need to perform a service you requested, compliance with legal or regulatory obligations, protection of life and safety during relief operations, fraud prevention, platform security, legitimate organizational interests, or the establishment, exercise, or defense of legal claims.</p>
        <p>Where consent is required, you may withdraw it through the appropriate platform or contact channel, subject to legal, operational, safety, and recordkeeping limitations. Withdrawal of consent may affect your ability to use features that depend on the information involved.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="information-disclosure" class="info-section">
        <h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We do not sell personal information. We may share information only when necessary for platform operations, safety, accountability, service delivery, or legal purposes.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may share information with providers that support hosting, email delivery, authentication, notifications, analytics, security, payment processing, file storage, and customer support.</li>
            <li><strong>Payment and Donation Partners:</strong> Donation details may be shared with payment processors, banks, e-wallet providers, or related financial partners to process, verify, refund, investigate, or reconcile payments.</li>
            <li><strong>Campaign Organizers and Administrators:</strong> Relevant donation, campaign, verification, or support information may be made available to authorized organizers or administrators when needed to manage campaigns, resolve concerns, or maintain accountability.</li>
            <li><strong>Volunteer and Event Coordinators:</strong> Event registration and role information may be shared with authorized coordinators for scheduling, attendance, safety, and communication purposes.</li>
            <li><strong>Partner Organizations:</strong> Limited information may be shared with trusted partners involved in relief operations, in-kind donation handling, volunteer coordination, beneficiary validation, or impact reporting.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal, Safety, and Rights Protection:</strong> We may disclose information if required by law, subpoena, court order, government request, or if we believe disclosure is necessary to investigate violations, protect beneficiaries, prevent fraud, protect platform users, or defend legal rights.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="donation-transparency" class="info-section">
        <h2>Donation Transparency and Public Information</h2>
        <p>Tulong Kabataan promotes transparent reporting. Campaign pages, donation summaries, impact reports, event pages, and campaign updates may display non-sensitive information such as campaign titles, fundraising progress, public descriptions, organizer names, donation totals, donor display names where applicable, and published updates.</p>
        <p>Users must avoid posting sensitive information about beneficiaries, donors, volunteers, minors, or private individuals unless they have proper authority and the disclosure is necessary, respectful, and lawful. We may edit, hide, or remove content that creates privacy, safety, dignity, or legal risk.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="data-security" class="info-section">
        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect personal information. These may include access controls, authentication, account verification, secure file handling, activity monitoring, limited administrator access, and operational review procedures.</p>
        <p>No website, server, database, or internet transmission is completely secure. Users are responsible for keeping their login credentials confidential, using strong passwords, signing out on shared devices, and reporting suspicious account activity promptly.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="retention" class="info-section">
        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We keep personal information only for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this policy, including account management, donation records, campaign accountability, impact reporting, safety, fraud prevention, dispute handling, legal compliance, audit requirements, and legitimate organizational records.</p>
        <p>Some records may be retained even after account deletion or a campaign ends when needed to protect beneficiaries, validate donations, comply with obligations, resolve disputes, investigate abuse, preserve financial records, or maintain public accountability for completed campaigns and reports.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="user-rights" class="info-section">
        <h2>User Rights</h2>
        <p>Subject to applicable law and verification of your identity, you may request access to your personal information, correction of inaccurate data, deletion or blocking of information when legally appropriate, withdrawal of consent, objection to certain processing, data portability where applicable, or information about how your data is processed.</p>
        <p>We may deny, limit, or defer a request when allowed by law, such as when the information is needed for legal claims, fraud prevention, financial records, ongoing investigations, campaign accountability, safety, or protection of another person's rights. We may ask for additional information to confirm your identity before acting on a request.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="children-privacy" class="info-section">
        <h2>Children and Youth Privacy</h2>
        <p>Tulong Kabataan serves youth-centered community work, but platform accounts, donations, campaign creation, event participation, and volunteer activities may require age-appropriate consent, supervision, or eligibility. Users must not submit personal information of minors unless they have authority to do so and the submission is necessary for a legitimate platform or program purpose.</p>
        <p>Photos, stories, IDs, addresses, school details, health information, or beneficiary information involving minors must be handled with extra care. We may remove content or request additional consent if we believe a submission could expose a child or young person to privacy, safety, dignity, or exploitation risks.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="cookies" class="info-section">
        <h2>Cookies, Logs, and Similar Technologies</h2>
        <p>We may use cookies, session data, device identifiers, and server logs to keep users signed in, protect accounts, remember preferences, analyze platform performance, prevent abuse, and improve user experience. Browser settings may allow you to block or delete cookies, but some platform features may not work properly without them.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="changes" class="info-section">
        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect platform improvements, legal requirements, security practices, or operational changes. The updated version will be posted on this page with a revised effective or last updated date. Continued use of the platform after changes are posted means you acknowledge the updated policy.</p>
